id: pm-3wsi
title: "Declarative extension install: activation failure is misreported and scaffold next_steps break when @unbrained/pm-cli is unresolvable"
description: "Installing a declarative (composeExtension) package into a workspace that cannot resolve @unbrained/pm-cli fails runtime activation ('Cannot find package'), yet pm install reports activated:true with runtime_activation_status:failed and failed_count:0 (contradictory). The failed install-time activation also skips item-type folder scaffolding, leaving a lingering health warning. Scaffold next_steps do not warn that the workspace must be able to resolve the SDK. Found in 2026-07-02 review (Lane B, pm-6vy7)."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: audit-followup,extensions,sdk
created_at: "2026-07-02T21:55:19.923Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-10T08:05:04.998Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-10T08:05:03.734Z"
author: claude-code-agent
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: Declarative extension install reports activation failure accurately and scaffold next_steps work when @unbrained/pm-cli is unresolvable; regression test covers the unresolvable-host path.
parent: pm-ugqx
risk: medium
confidence: high
resolution: "Made install load/activation failures authoritative, non-zero, and actionable with SDK recovery guidance."
expected_result: Failed activation is never reported as activated or successful.
actual_result: "Install returns ok=false, activated=false, degraded verification, diagnostics, recovery, and non-zero CLI exit."
